<br>
I am not sure what to think about that, after Wizards and Magicians wanting slow, Magicians constantly asking for root, now we got Magicians asking for concussion.<br>
<br>
First of all: they keep on claiming about how they have become the best dps class since PoP release, through a combination of really powerfull pets and good nukes upgrade.<br>
<br>
Why would they need more, since concussion (mixed with SCS3) will allow them to push out even more damage, thus reducing Wizards value, as for Nuking is the only thing we can do (raiding wizards comes to mind, in raid you seldom or never stun or root, or evac).<br>
<br>
Or maybe they realised they arent the masters of dps, and that they would need help?<br>
In this case, this has to be proven, because thats not the trend i saw when looking at various logs from magicians.<br>
<br>
I mean, i havent seen a single thread stating that &quot;Magicians dmg is broken&quot;, especially since PoP release.<br>
<br>
My take on this: Magicians came to realise that we rival (and sometimes outdamage them) in raid situations, as for dmg on raid mobs has always been where we truly shine, and now they want the best of all worlds, xp groups and raids.<br>
<br>
This was always agreed upon that the ability to summon a powerfull pet while beeing able to cast powerfull nukes would need some trades off: namely no root and snare for Magicians.<br>
<br>
I think the trade off also includes agro, if we want to remain a desirable class with still a specific niche.<br>
<br>
The most common objection about Magicians out damaging Wizards with nukes was always Cast time/ Agro multipliers, concussion.<br>
<br>
Now they want the same agro lowering tools as ours, claiming that built-in agro in our nukes is still lower; soon they will want the same buil-in agro reduction.<br>
<br>
Wizards never even seriously considered to ask for a pet, for the simple reason we could have made a Magician when we started EQ.<br>
<br>
If you really want to nuke better, at this moment of EQ evolution, i think you should re-roll a Wizard.<br>
<br>
<br>
Belarkan Mandragoran<br>
Arcanist of Vortex of Life<br>
Karana World Server.<br>
<br>
