High Priest of Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/7/03 10:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> It's a hard call. Most spell casting classes have some form or aggro reducing spells, some limited in what they can do. Ranger and druid harmony spells only work outdoors and the necro ones on undead.<br>
<br>
It doesn't look like shaman or beastloards have any aggro reducing spells. Wizards got a quest one with Kunark. And a quest that isn't easably done at level 39, though not impossible.<br>
<br>
Reading the thread, it seems that aggro from a pet being passed onto the mage is an issue. Some say it's never passed on, some say it is. Aggro is a tricky thing that no one understands. <br>
<br>
I doubt that aggro is ever passed on to another player. Mearly that some actions, such as healing, has it's aggro figured out like this:<br>
<br>
Melee A is fighting Mob A. Melee A has aggro, and alot of it. Healer A heals Melee A. The healing aggro is figured out based on the aggro Melee A has and some multiplier. Which means that the cleric suddenly has higher aggro then the main tank. I don't know if this is true, just my theroy, based on observations. <br>
<br>
I'm sure the same happens with mages and their pets when they heal thier pets. I wonder if a mage sent their pet in, prebuffed, and never cast a spell while the pet battled a mob, would the mage get aggro if the pet died during the battle? If they don't get aggro, then I would say no, they don't need this spell. <br>
<br>
However, mages seldom just stand by while thier pet does all the killing. Unless I'm mistaken, if the pet does all the damage, the player only gets 25% of the xp for the kill. This was a recent change over othe 50% damage/50% xp. If the mage does even a few points of damage, he gets full XP (assuming this is a mage versus 1 mob battle). So a mage seldom lets his pet do all the damage.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that a mages pet is thier aggro buff for them. But since letting the pet do all the work means they have to kill four mobs to get the XP of ones means most Mages won't do this. It's a trade off:<br>
<br>
Let pet do all the work (this means no healing pet) means slower XP (when soloing), but far safer.<br>
<br>
Helping pet kill mob is faster, but means higher risk. <br>
<br>
In the end, I don't think magicians need an aggro reducing spell. Magicians work through their pets. Earth elementals, root, air stuns. Pets also work as a buffer of HPS for the magician, unless the magician does something to out aggro thier own pet. <br>
<br>
The more we blur the lines between classes, the less reason there are to have classes.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 6696<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/7/03 12:54 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> They can have a lesser version of the level 39 concussion... but anything more than that and I'll be kind of pissed off.  Mostly because it will probably be easier to obtain than our 39 version and our virtually non-existant ultra limited level 60 version. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2723<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/7/03 1:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> &gt;It's a hard call. Most spell casting classes have some form or aggro reducing spells, some limited in what they can do. <br>
