<br>
Healing a player on an NPCs hate list generates hate like nuking that mob.  The amount of hate the person you are healing doesn't seem to matter.  The same goes for buffs.<br>
<br>
The Taunt and Evade abilities that tanks and rogues get depend on what other players aggro is.  A successful taunt kicks the player to the top of the hate list, which is very very useful.  A successful evade will drop you at least 1 place on the hate list, also useful.  They may have additional hate effects.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>he only actual classes that have personal aggro reduction are Rogues (evade and escape), Wizards (Concussion), Rangers (jolt), and Bards (escape). Personal aggro reduction is what is useful in fights, memblur is much too situational.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Enchanters: Boggle, Guise line.  Mana hogs.<br>
Bards: 900 mana self-mem blur.  This is bard mana remember.<br>
SK/Monks/Necros: FD<br>
